### ============================================================
### RallyAPI — E2E Test Flow
### Tests the complete order lifecycle:
### Login → Place Order → Confirm → Dispatch → Assign → 
### PickUp → Deliver → Verify
### ============================================================
### 
### PREREQUISITES:
### 1. Run seed-test-data.sql first
### 2. App running on https://localhost:5001 (or adjust @baseUrl)
### 3. All Phases 0-2 completed (event handlers wired up)
###
### HOW TO USE:
### - In VS Code: Install "REST Client" extension
### - In Rider: Use built-in HTTP client
### - Run requests sequentially (top to bottom)
### - Copy values from responses into variables as noted
### ============================================================

@baseUrl = https://localhost:7041


### ============================================================
### STEP 1: Customer Login — Send OTP
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/otp/send
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "9876543210"}

### Expected: 200 OK
### In dev mode, OTP is likely "123456" or logged to console


### ============================================================
### STEP 2: Customer Login — Verify OTP & Get JWT
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/customers/otp/verify
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "9876543210", "otp": "123456"}

### Expected: 200 OK with JWT token
### >>> COPY the token value into @customerToken below
@customerToken = dummy-token


### ============================================================
### STEP 3: Restaurant Owner Login — Send OTP
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "+919876500001"}


### ============================================================
### STEP 4: Restaurant Owner Login — Verify OTP & Get JWT
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "+919876500001", "otp": "123456"}

### >>> COPY the token into @restaurantToken below
@restaurantToken = PASTE_RESTAURANT_JWT_HERE


### ============================================================
### STEP 5: Rider Login — Send OTP
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "+919876500002"}


### ============================================================
### STEP 6: Rider Login — Verify OTP & Get JWT
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "+919876500002", "otp": "123456"}

### >>> COPY the token into @riderToken below
@riderToken = PASTE_RIDER_JWT_HERE


### ============================================================
### STEP 7: Admin Login — Send OTP
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/send-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "+919876500003"}


### ============================================================
### STEP 8: Admin Login — Verify OTP & Get JWT
### ============================================================
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/users/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{"phoneNumber": "+919876500003", "otp": "123456"}

### >>> COPY the token into @adminToken below
@adminToken = PASTE_ADMIN_JWT_HERE


### ============================================================
### STEP 9: Browse Restaurant Menu
### ============================================================
@restaurantId = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010

GET {{baseUrl}}/api/catalog/restaurants/{{restaurantId}}/menus
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### Expected: 200 OK with menu items (Butter Chicken, Paneer Tikka, Garlic Naan)
### Note the menu item IDs for the order


### ============================================================
### STEP 10: Get Delivery Price Quote
### ============================================================
### Pickup: Koramangala restaurant | Delivery: Indiranagar customer
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/delivery/quote
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "pickupLatitude": 12.9352,
  "pickupLongitude": 77.6245,
  "deliveryLatitude": 12.9784,
  "deliveryLongitude": 77.6408,
  "restaurantId": "00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000010"
}

### Expected: 200 OK with quoteId and fee breakdown
### >>> COPY the quoteId into @quoteId below
@quoteId = PASTE_QUOTE_ID_HERE


### ============================================================
### STEP 11: Place Order
### ============================================================
@menuItem1Id = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000031
@menuItem2Id = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000032
@menuItem3Id = 00000000-0000-0000-0000-000000000033

POST {{baseUrl}}/api/orders
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "restaurantId": "{{restaurantId}}",
  "deliveryAddress": {
    "street": "100 Feet Road, Indiranagar",
    "city": "Bengaluru",
    "state": "Karnataka",
    "zipCode": "560038",
    "latitude": 12.9784,
    "longitude": 77.6408
  },
  "items": [
    {
      "menuItemId": "{{menuItem1Id}}",
      "menuItemName": "Butter Chicken",
      "quantity": 1,
      "unitPrice": 280.00
    },
    {
      "menuItemId": "{{menuItem3Id}}",
      "menuItemName": "Garlic Naan",
      "quantity": 2,
      "unitPrice": 60.00
    }
  ],
  "quoteId": "{{quoteId}}",
  "specialInstructions": "Extra spicy please"
}

### Expected: 201 Created with orderId
### >>> COPY the orderId into @orderId below
@orderId = PASTE_ORDER_ID_HERE


### ============================================================
### STEP 12: Check Order Status (should be "Placed")
### ============================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### Expected: Status = "Placed" or "Pending"


### ============================================================
### STEP 13: Restaurant Confirms Order 🔥 KEY STEP
### ============================================================
### This triggers the ENTIRE event chain:
###   OrderConfirmedEvent (domain)
###   → OrderConfirmedDomainEventHandler (Phase 1 bridge)
###   → OrderConfirmedIntegrationEvent
###   → Delivery creates DeliveryRequest
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/confirm
Authorization: Bearer {{restaurantToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "estimatedPrepTimeMinutes": 20
}

### Expected: 200 OK, Order status = "Confirmed"


### ============================================================
### STEP 14: Verify DeliveryRequest Was Created ✅ Phase 1 Proof
### ============================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/delivery/requests?orderId={{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Expected: 200 OK with a DeliveryRequest for this orderId
### >>> COPY the deliveryRequestId into @deliveryRequestId below
@deliveryRequestId = PASTE_DELIVERY_REQUEST_ID_HERE


### ============================================================
### STEP 15: Restaurant Marks Order Ready for Pickup
### ============================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}/ready
Authorization: Bearer {{restaurantToken}}

### Expected: 200 OK, triggers OrderReadyForPickupIntegrationEvent
### This kicks off rider dispatch in the Delivery module


### ============================================================
### STEP 16: Admin Triggers Dispatch (if not auto-dispatched)
### ============================================================
### The dispatch orchestrator should find our seeded rider
### (online, KYC-approved, within search radius)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/delivery/requests/{{deliveryRequestId}}/dispatch
Authorization: Bearer {{adminToken}}

### Expected: 200 OK, rider dispatch process begins


### ============================================================
### STEP 17: Check Order — Should Show Rider Info ✅ Phase 2 Proof
### ============================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### Expected: riderId, riderName, riderPhone populated
### ✅ Proves DeliveryRiderAssignedEventHandler works!


### ============================================================
### STEP 18: Rider Marks Picked Up
### ============================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/delivery/requests/{{deliveryRequestId}}/pickup
Authorization: Bearer {{riderToken}}

### Expected: 200 OK


### ============================================================
### STEP 19: Check Order — Should be "PickedUp"
### ============================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### Expected: Status = "PickedUp"
### ✅ Proves DeliveryPickedUpEventHandler works!


### ============================================================
### STEP 20: Rider Marks Delivered 🎯 FINAL ACTION
### ============================================================
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/delivery/requests/{{deliveryRequestId}}/deliver
Authorization: Bearer {{riderToken}}

### Expected: 200 OK


### ============================================================
### STEP 21: FINAL CHECK — Order Status = "Delivered" 🎉
### ============================================================
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{orderId}}
Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}

### 🎉🎉🎉 Expected: Status = "Delivered", rider info attached
### THE E2E FLOW IS COMPLETE!


### ============================================================
###                    FAILURE PATH TESTS
### ============================================================

### --- Cancel Order (before confirmation) ---
### Place a fresh order, then:
# PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{newOrderId}}/cancel
# Authorization: Bearer {{customerToken}}
# Content-Type: application/json
# {"reason": "Changed my mind"}

### --- Reject Order (restaurant rejects) ---
# PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/orders/{{newOrderId}}/reject
# Authorization: Bearer {{restaurantToken}}
# Content-Type: application/json
# {"reason": "Kitchen closing soon"}

### --- Delivery Failed ---
### Walk through full flow to dispatch, then:
# PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/delivery/requests/{{newDeliveryRequestId}}/fail
# Authorization: Bearer {{riderToken}}
# Content-Type: application/json
# {"reason": "Customer unreachable"}
### ✅ Proves DeliveryFailedEventHandler works!


### ============================================================
### DB VERIFICATION QUERY (run in psql/pgAdmin after Step 21)
### ============================================================
### SELECT id, status, rider_id, rider_name, rider_phone, updated_at
### FROM orders.orders WHERE id = '{orderId}';
###
### Expected: status='Delivered', rider fields NOT NULL
